        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 3. Vercoia interrupta sp. nov. Female holotype (CL 4.0 mm, NFU 530-2-2500). Appendages dissected from left side. (A) Third maxilliped, lateral; (B) same, distal two segments, dorsal; (C) first pereopod, lateral; (D) same, chela and carpus, dorsal; (E) second pereopod, lateral; (F) same, dactylus, propodus and carpus, mesial; (G) third pereopod, lateral; (H) fourth pereopod, lateral; (I) same, dactylus and distal part of propodus; (J) fifth pereopod, lateral; (K) first pleopod, ventral; (L) second pleopod, ventral." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4658755/files/figure.png" .

